h4. Summary

I observed the following build warning compiling PHPC after upgrading to Ubuntu 22.04:

{noformat}
/phpc/src/libmongoc/src/libmongoc/src/mongoc/mongoc-openssl.c: In function ‘_mongoc_openssl_init’:
/phpc/src/libmongoc/src/libmongoc/src/mongoc/mongoc-openssl.c:79:4: warning: ‘ERR_load_BIO_strings’ is deprecated: Since OpenSSL 3.0 [-Wdeprecated-declarations]
   79 |    ERR_load_BIO_strings ();
      |    ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
In file included from /usr/include/openssl/cryptoerr.h:17,
                 from /usr/include/openssl/crypto.h:38,
                 from /usr/include/openssl/bio.h:30,
                 from /phpc/src/libmongoc/src/libmongoc/src/mongoc/mongoc-openssl.c:23:
/usr/include/openssl/cryptoerr_legacy.h:31:27: note: declared here
   31 | OSSL_DEPRECATEDIN_3_0 int ERR_load_BIO_strings(void);
      |
{noformat}

Quoting [OPENSSL 3.0: Main Changes from OpenSSL 1.1.1|https://www.openssl.org/docs/manmaster/man7/migration_guide.html]:

{quote}
ERR_load_*(), ERR_func_error_string(), ERR_get_error_line(), ERR_get_error_line_data(), ERR_get_state()

OpenSSL now loads error strings automatically so these functions are not needed.
{quote}

See [rsyslog/rsyslog@e5b6d36|https://github.com/rsyslog/rsyslog/commit/e5b6d36e4c38e458bc12ac3c9ba6bea727ce0f19#diff-1cdc1bd9f7ef488180b52b445dec74866b45bcf8957bbe1b95b30eea22c2da1bR424] for a related fix.

h4. Environment

 * Ubuntu 22.04.02 LTS
 * gcc version 11.3.0 (Ubuntu 11.3.0-1ubuntu1~22.04)
 * OpenSSL 3.0.2 15 Mar 2022 (Library: OpenSSL 3.0.2 15 Mar 2022)

h4. Summary

Mongo with higher volume of connections may return connectionId as double during the handshake process. The {*}C{*}(1.23.2) & {*}C++{*}(3.7.x)drivers fail to do a [type check|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-c-driver/blob/1.23.2/src/libmongoc/src/mongoc/mongoc-server-description.c#L743] for double type connectionId in hello/ismaster response and hence fails to connect to mongo.

This happens in clusters with a high volume of connections created at a higher rate and/or without any connection pooling mechanism.

db.isMaster() response from mongo shell:
{noformat}
    db.isMaster()
    {
        "ismaster" : true,
        "msg" : "isdbgrid",
      ...
      ...
      "connectionId" : 3177689371,
      ...
      ...
    }{noformat}
 

db.isMaster() response from *python* driver:

 
{noformat}
{
   'ok': 1.0, 
   'msg': 'isdbgrid', 
   'ismaster': True, 
   ...
   ...  
   'connectionId': 3177722651.0, <==== double value
   ...
   ...
}{noformat}
 

The C driver fails to check connectionId value, 3177722651.0 with [BSON_ITER_HOLDS_INT|https://github.com/mongodb/libbson/blob/master/src/bson/bson-iter.h#L90]
h4. Environment

 _C / CXX driver versions:_ 

 
{noformat}
{"name":"mongoc / mongocxx","version":"1.23.1 / 3.7.0"}
{"name":"mongoc / mongocxx","version":"1.23.2 / 3.7.0"} 
{noformat}
 _C / CXX compiler and version:_ 

 
{noformat}
gcc (Ubuntu 5.4.0-6ubuntu1~16.04.12) 5.4.0 20160609
c++11 & c++17
{noformat}
 

Mongo:
{noformat}
Sharded Cluster with v4.4.14
{noformat}
h4. How to Reproduce

It's difficult to reproduce the issue. Need to create connections at a higher rate to overflow {{int32}} value of {{connectionId.}}
h4. Temporary Fix

Restarting the mongo service would reset the {{connectionId counter.}}

h4. Summary

As part of the development of the [serverless proxy|https://github.com/10gen/serverless-proxy], which is an Envoy process with custom filters to transcode the wire protocol into gRPC that will be used in Atlas Serverless, we are using some internal functionality of the C driver to perform wire protocol parsing (basically using {{_mongoc_rpc_scatter}} and various other functions).

We noticed that the serverless proxy segfaults when parsing an {{OP_MSG}} with the optional CRC checksum present. This occurs during the initial SASL handshake when connecting to Envoy using the legacy shell. The segfault occurs in {{{}_mongoc_rpc_scatter_msg{}}}, which is invoked by {{{}_mongoc_rpc_scatter{}}}.

After some initial digging, I think the use of {{strlen}} [here|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-c-driver/blob/e24a7a2eb6486d142dd13a0472d76ff25188ed12/src/libmongoc/src/mongoc/mongoc-rpc.c#L519-L523] is unsafe. In fact, I think we should be using {{strnlen}} everywhere in {{mongoc-rpc.c}} as a precaution.

Below is an example of a buffer that causes {{_mongoc_rpc_scatter}} to segfault:
